Job Description
Share
Responsible for supervision of Chinese Kitchen. Guides various cooks in performance of their duties to the required standards.
Assist the Executive Chef with special functions/food promotions.
Expedites food order in the kitchen to facilitate efficient restaurant service.
Keeps in view the following days menu and requisition for food items needed from various stores
Assigned to conduct on the job training and improve the standard when necessary.
In charge of duty rosters and organize shift.
Maintains all office records and other inter-office correspondence.
Responsible for hygiene and safety conditions in the kitchen.
To administer and properly control the subordinate staff and check the performance and reports to department head as and when required and suggest the remedial measures.
Graduate from recognized culinary college, preference will be given to post graduate culinary education.
Professional Experience :10-15 years in the 4/5 star hotel, in the hotel kitchen as Chinese Chef
Keyword: Chinese Chef
